<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id798ae1f9-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s1608"><num value="1608">§ 1608.</num><heading> Views of other agencies</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In the exercise of its functions under this subchapter, the Bureau may obtain upon requests the views of any other Federal agency which, in the judgment of the Bureau, exercises regulatory or supervisory functions with respect to any class of creditors subject to this subchapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id798ae1fa-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">(<ref href="/us/pl/90/321/tI/s109">Pub. L. 90–321, title I, § 109</ref>, <date date="1968-05-29">May 29, 1968</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/82/150">82 Stat. 150</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/111/203/tX/s1100A/2">Pub. L. 111–203, title X, § 1100A(2)</ref>, <date date="2010-07-21">July 21, 2010</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/124/2107">124 Stat. 2107</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
